k1             = \n|data1              = \n|blank2             = \n|data2              = \n|blank3             = \n|data3              = \n|blank4             = \n|data4              = \n|blank5             = \n|data5              = \n}}\n\n'''Queenstar Maame Pokua Sawyerr''' (born 1 July 1964) is a [[Ghana]]ian politician and the former deputy [[Central Region (Ghana)|Central Region]]al Minister of Ghana.<ref name=min>{{cite web|title=List of Regional Ministers in Ghana with Their Deputies.|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/469518/1/list-of-regional-ministers-in-ghana-with-their-dep.html|publisher=www.modernghana.com|accessdate=23 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"sdf\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/features/artikel.php?ID=277257 | title=List of Regional Ministers in Ghana with Their Deputies | publisher=www.ghanaweb.com | accessdate=23 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=jmnko>{{cite web|title=Regional Ministers |url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/2012-02-08-08-18-09/regional-ministers |publisher=www.ghana.gov.ghs |accessdate=23 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014214651/http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/2012-02-08-08-18-09/regional-ministers |archivedate=14 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=19|title=Parliament of Ghana|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nSawyerr was born in Agona Kwanyako, Central Region.<ref name=\"mps\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=5405|title=Ghana MPs - MP Details - Sawyerr, Queenstar Pokuah|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref> She received her higher national diploma from [[Accra Polytechnic]] and received a bachelor's degree in Business Administration and master's in Public Administration from [[Atlantic International University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ukgcc.com.gh/hon-queenstar-pokuah-sawyerr-2/|title=HON. QUEENSTAR POKUAH SAWYERR|date=2018-07-05|publisher=UK-Ghana Chamber of Commerce|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-25}}</ref><ref name=\"mps\"/>\n\n== Career ==\nShe is a business woman and a politician.<ref name=\"mps\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nShe is married with four children.<ref name=\"mps\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sawyerr, Queenstar Maame Pokua}}\n[[Category:National Democratic Congress (Ghana) politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Ghana]]\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix = Hon.  \n|name        = Queenster Maame Pokua Sawyerr\n|honorific-suffix = \n|image       = \n|alt         = \n|caption     = \n|constituency_MP =\n|parliament  =\n|majority    =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by adding a number-->\n|term_start  =  \n|term_end    =  \n|predecessor =   \n|successor   =  \n|order2             =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by changing the number-->\n|office2            =  \n|term_start2        =  \n|term_end2          =  \n|president2         = [[John Dramani Mahama]]\n|predecessor2       =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by changing the number-->\n|successor2         =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by changing the number-->\n|order3             =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by changing the number-->\n|office3            =  \n|term_start3        =  \n|term_end3          =  \n|president3         =  \n|predecessor3       =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by changing the number-->\n|successor3         =  <!--Can be repeated up to eight times by changing the number-->\n|birth_date         = \n|birth_place        = Ghana\n|death_date         = \n|death_place        = \n|restingplace       = \n|restingplacecoordinates = \n|birthname          = \n|nationality        = Ghanaian\n|party              = [[National Democratic Congress (Ghana)|NDC]]\n|otherparty         =  <!--For additional political affiliations-->\n|spouse             = \n|partner            =  <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n|relations          = \n|children           = \n|residence          = \n|alma_mater         = \n|occupation         = \n|profession         = \n|cabinet            = \n|committees         = \n|portfolio          = \n|religion           =\n|signature          = \n|signature_alt      = \n|website            = \n|footnotes          = \n|blank1             = \n|data1              = \n|blank2             = \n|data2              = \n|blank3             = \n|data3              = \n|blank4             = \n|data4              = \n|blank5             = \n|data5              = \n}}\n\n'''Queenstar Maame Pokua Sawyerr''' (born 1 July 1964) is a [[Ghana]]ian politician and the deputy [[Central Region (Ghana)|Central Region]]al Minister of Ghana.<ref name=min>{{cite web|title=List of Regional Ministers in Ghana with Their Deputies.|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/469518/1/list-of-regional-ministers-in-ghana-with-their-dep.html|publisher=www.modernghana.com|accessdate=23 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"sdf\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/features/artikel.php?ID=277257 | title=List of Regional Ministers in Ghana with Their Deputies | publisher=www.ghanaweb.com | accessdate=23 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=jmnko>{{cite web|title=Regional Ministers |url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/2012-02-08-08-18-09/regional-ministers |publisher=www.ghana.gov.ghs |accessdate=23 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014214651/http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/2012-02-08-08-18-09/regional-ministers |archivedate=14 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=19|title=Parliament of Ghana|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nSawyerr was born in Agona Kwanyako, Central Region.<ref name=\"mps\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=5405|title=Ghana MPs - MP Details - Sawyerr, Queenstar Pokuah|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref> She received her higher national diploma from [[Accra Polytechnic]] and received a bachelor's degree in Business Administration and master's in Public Administration from [[Atlantic International University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ukgcc.com.gh/hon-queenstar-pokuah-sawyerr-2/|title=HON. QUEENSTAR POKUAH SAWYERR|date=2018-07-05|publisher=UK-Ghana Chamber of Commerce|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-25}}</ref><ref name=\"mps\"/>\n\n== Career ==\nShe is a business woman and a politician.<ref name=\"mps\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nShe is married with four children.<ref name=\"mps\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sawyerr, Queenstar Maame Pokua}}\n[[Category:National Democratic Congress (Ghana) politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Ghana]]\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Kobby Dankwah", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queenstar_Pokuah_Sawyerr"}
{"title_page": "Kosovo women's national under-18 basketball team", "text_new": "{{one source|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox national basketball team\n| country            = Kosovo\n| logo               = Flag of Kosovo.svg\n| logo_width         = 130px\n| nickname           =\n| fiba_zone          = FIBA Europe\n| national_fed       = Kosovo Basketball Federation\n| coach              = \n| wc_championship    = [[FIBA Under-19 Women's Basketball World Cup|U19 World Cup]]\n| wc_appearances     = None\n| wc_medals          = \n| zone_championship  = [[FIBA U18 Women's European Championship|U18 European Championship]]\n| zone_appearances   = None\n| zone_medals        = \n| zone_championship2 = [[FIBA U18 Women's European Championship#Division B|U18 European Championship Division B]]\n| zone_appearances2  = 2\n| zone_medals2       = None\n| zone_championship3 = [[FIBA U18 Women's European Championship#Division C|U18 European Championship Division C]]\n| zone_appearances3  = 2\n| zone_medals3       = None\n}}\n\nThe '''Kosovo women's national under-18 basketball team''' is a national [[basketball]] team of [[Kosovo]], administered by the [[Kosovo Basketball Federation]].<ref>[http://www.fiba.basketball/federation/Kosovo Profile - Kosovo], FIBA.basketball</ref>\nIt represents the country in women's international under-18 basketball competitions.\n\n==Championship participations==\n*[[2016 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division C]] \u2013 5th place\n*[[2017 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division C]] \u2013 5th place\n*[[2018 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division B]] \u2013 22nd place\n*[[2019 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division B]] \u2013 22nd place\n\n==See also==\n*[[Kosovo women's national under-20 basketball team]]\n*[[Kosovo women's national under-16 basketball team]]\n*[[Kosovo men's national under-18 basketball team]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.fiba.basketball/pages/eng/fa/p/rpp/150/tid/98425/_//teams.html Archived records] of Kosovo team participations\n\n{{National sports teams of Kosovo}}\n\n[[Category:Basketball in Kosovo]]\n[[Category:Women's national under-18 basketball teams]]\n[[Category:Kosovo national youth basketball teams|U]]\n\n\n{{Europe-basketball-team-stub}}\n{{Kosovo-sport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{one source|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox national basketball team\n| country            = Kosovo\n| logo               = Flag of Kosovo.svg\n| logo_width         = 130px\n| nickname           =\n| fiba_zone          = FIBA Europe\n| national_fed       = Kosovo Basketball Federation\n| coach              = \n| wc_championship    = [[FIBA Under-19 Women's Basketball World Cup|U19 World Cup]]\n| wc_appearances     = None\n| wc_medals          = \n| zone_championship  = [[FIBA U18 Women's European Championship|U18 European Championship]]\n| zone_appearances   = None\n| zone_medals        = \n| zone_championship2 = [[FIBA U18 Women's European Championship#Division B|U18 European Championship Division B]]\n| zone_appearances2  = 2\n| zone_medals2       = None\n| zone_championship3 = [[FIBA U18 Women's European Championship#Division C|U18 European Championship Division C]]\n| zone_appearances3  = 2\n| zone_medals3       = None\n}}\n\nThe '''Kosovo women's national under-18 basketball team''' is a national [[basketball]] team of [[Kosovo]], administered by the [[Kosovo Basketball Federation]].<ref>[http://www.fiba.basketball/federation/Kosovo Profile - Kosovo], FIBA.basketball</ref>\nIt represents the country in women's international under-18 basketball competitions.\n\n==Championship participations==\n*[[2016 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division C]] \u2013 5th place\n*[[2017 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division C]] \u2013 5th place\n*[[2018 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division B]] \u2013 22nd place\n*[[2019 FIBA U18 Women's European Championship Division B]] \u2013 22nd place\n\n==See also==\n*[[Kosovo women's national under-20 basketball team]]\n*[[Kosovo women's national under-16 basketball team]]\n*[[Kosovo men's national under-18 basketball team]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.fiba.basketball/pages/eng/fa/p/rpp/150/tid/98425/_//teams.html Archived records] of Kosovo team participations\n\n{{National sports teams of Kosovo}}\n\n[[Category:Basketball in Kosovo]]\n[[Category:Women's national under-18 basketball teams]]\n[[Category:Kosovo national youth basketball teams|U]]\n\n{{stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rpyle731", "label": "safe", "comment": "stub sort", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kosovo_women%27s_national_under-18_basketball_team"}
{"title_page": "Ar\u00f3n Piper", "text_new": "{{short description|Actor espa\u00f1ol}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ar\u00f3n Piper\n| image              = Ar\u00f3n Piper in the film 2019 Los Rodr\u00edguez y el m\u00e1s all\u00e1.jpg\n| caption            = Piper as Jacobo in the 2019 film ''Los Rodr\u00edguez y el m\u00e1s all\u00e1''\n| birth_name         = Ar\u00f3n Julio Manuel Piper Barbero\n| birth_place        = [[Berlin]], Germany\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|March 29, 1997}}<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| citizenship        = {{flatlist|\n*Germany\n*Spain}}\n| occupation         = Actor and Singer\n| years_active       = 2004\u2013present\n| partner            = \n}}\n\n'''Ar\u00f3n Piper''' (born March 29, 1997)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Urzaiz|first=Bego\u00f1a G\u00f3mez|url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2020/03/17/icon/1584444955_197829.html|title=Ar\u00f3n Piper: \u201cEs una locura lo que te pagan. Sigo alucinando y mi entorno tambi\u00e9n\u201d|date=2020-03-18|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=2020-03-23|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref> is a German/Spanish actor known for playing Ander Mu\u00f1oz in the [[Netflix]] [[teen drama]] ''[[\u00c9lite (TV series)|\u00c9lite]]''.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.elpais.com/elpais/2019/09/16/inenglish/1568636024_089185.html|title=Meet the most sought-after young men in Madrid|last=Pastor|first=Custodio|date=2019-09-17|website=EL PA\u00cdS|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe was born in [[Berlin]], [[Germany]].<ref name=\":0\" /> His father is German and his mother is Spanish. He has a younger brother.<ref name=\":0\" /> When Ar\u00f3n was 5 years old, they moved to [[Spain]]. He has studied acting and directing. He is also interested in doing music. <ref name=\":0\" /> Recently came out with a single called \"Sigo\" along with other musicians. He can speak four languages: [[Castilian Spanish]], [[Catalan language|Catalan]], [[German language|German]], and [[English language|English]].\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{unsourced section|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Film ===\n*''The Gunman'' (2004)\n*''Maktub'' (2011)\n*''Fracaso escolar'' (2012)\n*''Only when I have nothing to eat'' (2012)\n*''15 A\u00f1os y un dia'' (2013) \n*''La Corona Partida'' (2016)\n*''Un Minuto'' (2018)\n*''Los Rodr\u00edguez y el m\u00e1s all\u00e1'' (2019).                                 *Elite(2019)\n\n=== Television ===\n*''Centro M\u00e9dico'' (2016-2017)\n*''[[\u00c9lite (TV series)|\u00c9lite]]'' (2018-TBA)<ref>It is currently unknown if Piper is returning for Season 4 of \u00c9lite</ref>\n*''Derecho a so\u00f1ar'' (2019)\n*''El desorden que dejas'' (2020)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Piper, Aron}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Berlin]]\n[[Category:German male television actors]]\n[[Category:German male film actors]]\n[[Category:German emigrants to Spain]]\n[[Category:Spanish people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Spanish male television actors]]\n[[Category:Spanish male film actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century German male actors]]\n\n{{actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Actor espa\u00f1ol}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ar\u00f3n Piper\n| image              = Ar\u00f3n Piper in the film 2019 Los Rodr\u00edguez y el m\u00e1s all\u00e1.jpg\n| caption            = Piper as Jacobo in the 2019 film ''Los Rodr\u00edguez y el m\u00e1s all\u00e1''\n| birth_name         = Ar\u00f3n Julio Manuel Piper Barbero\n| birth_place        = [[Berlin]], Germany\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|March 29, 1997}}<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| citizenship        = {{flatlist|\n*Germany\n*Spain}}\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2004\u2013present\n| partner            = \n}}\n\n'''Ar\u00f3n Piper''' (born March 29, 1997)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Urzaiz|first=Bego\u00f1a G\u00f3mez|url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2020/03/17/icon/1584444955_197829.html|title=Ar\u00f3n Piper: \u201cEs una locura lo que te pagan. Sigo alucinando y mi entorno tambi\u00e9n\u201d|date=2020-03-18|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=2020-03-23|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref> is a German/Spanish actor known for playing Ander Mu\u00f1oz in the [[Netflix]] [[teen drama]] ''[[\u00c9lite (TV series)|\u00c9lite]]''.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.elpais.com/elpais/2019/09/16/inenglish/1568636024_089185.html|title=Meet the most sought-after young men in Madrid|last=Pastor|first=Custodio|date=2019-09-17|website=EL PA\u00cdS|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe was born in [[Berlin]], [[Germany]].<ref name=\":0\" /> His father is German and his mother is Spanish.<ref name=\":0\" /> When Ar\u00f3n was 5 years old, they moved to [[Spain]]. He has studied acting and directing. He is also interested in doing music. <ref name=\":0\" /> Recently came out with a single called \"Sigo\" along with other musicians. He can speak four languages: [[Castilian Spanish]], [[Catalan language|Catalan]], [[German language|German]], and [[English language|English]].\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{unsourced section|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Film ===\n*''The Gunman'' (2004)\n*''Maktub'' (2011)\n*''Fracaso escolar'' (2012)\n*''Only when I have nothing to eat'' (2012)\n*''15 A\u00f1os y un dia'' (2013) \n*''La Corona Partida'' (2016)\n*''Un Minuto'' (2018)\n*''Los Rodr\u00edguez y el m\u00e1s all\u00e1'' (2019).                                 *Elite(2019)\n\n=== Television ===\n*''Centro M\u00e9dico'' (2016-2017)\n*''[[\u00c9lite (TV series)|\u00c9lite]]'' (2018-TBA)<ref>It is currently unknown if Piper is returning for Season 4 of \u00c9lite</ref>\n*''Derecho a so\u00f1ar'' (2019)\n*''El desorden que dejas'' (2020)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Piper, Aron}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]