{"title_page": "III (Maylene and the Sons of Disaster album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = III\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Maylene and the Sons of Disaster]]\n| cover      = MAYLENE_IIIcover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = June 23, 2009\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]]|[[Southern rock]]}}\n| length     = 38:56\n| label      = [[Ferret Music]]\n| producer   = Jason Elgin\n| prev_title = [[II (Maylene and the Sons of Disaster)|II]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = [[IV (Maylene and the Sons of Disaster album)|IV]]\n| next_year  = 2011\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = III\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Just a Shock\n | single1date = May 8, 2009\n | single2     = Step Up (I'm On It)\n | single2date = August 11, 2009\n | single3     = Listen Close\n | single3date = March 29, 2011\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{rating|4|5}} <ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1573201}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]''\n| rev2Score =  {{Rating|1.5|5}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://altpress.com/reviews/III.htm |title=Alternative Press &#124; Reviews |publisher=Altpress.com |date= |accessdate=2012-02-24}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''III''''' is the third studio album by [[Maylene and the Sons of Disaster]]. It was released June 23, 2009, and all pre-orders shipped on June 18, 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view&friendId=5302690&blogId=492915797 |title=Pre Order the New Album Here. **OUT JUNE 23rd!** van Maylene and the Sons of Disaster op Myspace |publisher=Blogs.myspace.com |date=2009-06-04 |accessdate=2012-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207065936/http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view |archive-date=2009-02-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The first single from the album is Just A Shock, which was uploaded to the band's MySpace as a promo for the album. About a week before the album's release another song was released to the public: Step Up (I'm On It). On June 19 the album was leaked in its entirety onto the internet. The song \"Harvest Moon Hanging\" is a reference to the Harvest Moon from the ''[[Bone (comics)|Bone]]'' series (most notably collection six, ''[[Old Man's Cave]]''). The album debuted at number 71 on the Billboard 200 in its first week of release. It was announced that their song \"Step Up (I'm on It)\" was used as the official theme for the inaugural [[Bragging Rights (2009)|WWE Bragging Rights]] Pay-Per-View. In 2010, was released a Deluxe Edition of the album in iTunes, containing two new songs and the music video for \"Step Up (I'm on It)\". \"Step Up (I'm on It)\" also was on Season Two: Episode One of the critically acclaimed series \"[[Sons Of Anarchy]]\", when Bobby came back to the clubhouse after his jail time. \"Step Up (I'm on It) is also in the video game ''[[EA Sports MMA]]''.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{track listing\n| all_lyrics   = [[Dallas Taylor (vocalist)|Dallas Taylor]]\n| all_music    = [[Maylene and the Sons of Disaster]]\n| title1       = Waiting on My Deathbed\n| length1      = 4:03\n| title2       = Settling Scores by Burning Bridges\n| length2      = 3:52\n| title3       = Just a Shock\n| length3      = 3:13\n| title4       = Last Train Coming\n| length4      = 2:31\n| title5       = Step Up (I'm on It)\n| length5      = 3:28\n| title6       = Listen Close\n| length6      = 3:40\n| title7       = The Old Iron Hills\n| length7      = 2:33\n| title8       = No Good Son\n| length8      = 2:49\n| title9       = Harvest Moon Hanging\n| length9      = 3:24\n| title10      = Oh Lonely Grave\n| length10     = 3:24\n| title11      = The End is Here... The End Is Beautiful\n| length11     = 5:11\n| total_length = 38:56\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline  = Deluxe edition bonus tracks\n| collapsed = yes\n| title12   = Where the Saints Roam\n| length12  = 3:42\n| title13   = Cheap Thrills Cost the Most\n| length13  = 3:20\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n;Maylene and the Sons of Disaster\n* [[Dallas Taylor (vocalist)|Dallas Taylor]] \u2013 lead vocals, banjo, acoustic guitar on \"Where the Saints Roam\"\n* Chad Huff \u2013 lead guitar\n* Jake Duncan \u2013 rhythm guitar, vocals\n* Kelly Scott Nunn \u2013 rhythm guitar\n* Roman Haviland \u2013 bass\n* Matt Clark \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n;Additional personnel\n* Bethany Borg \u2013 violin\n* Jacob Bunton \u2013 banjo, mandolin, violin, additional vocals\n* Tim Carroll \u2013 bowed bass\n* Billy Grant \u2013 harmonica, additional vocals\n* Chris Griffin \u2013 dobro, lap steel guitar\n* Keith Harrison \u2013 additional vocals\n* Michael Swann \u2013 slide guitar\n* Barry Waldrep \u2013 banjo, lap steel guitar, dobro\n* Adam Wright \u2013 piano, string arrangements\n* Jason Elgin \u2013 engineer, production, mixing, percussion, additional vocals\n* Roger Lian \u2013 mastering\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Maylene and the Sons of Disaster}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Iii}}\n[[Category:2009 albums]]\n[[Category:Maylene and the Sons of Disaster albums|03]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = III\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Maylene and the Sons of Disaster]]\n| cover      = MAYLENE_IIIcover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = June 23, 2009\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Hard rock]]|[[Southern metal]]}}\n| length     = 38:56\n| label      = [[Ferret Music]]\n| producer   = Jason Elgin\n| prev_title = [[II (Maylene and the Sons of Disaster)|II]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = [[IV (Maylene and the Sons of Disaster album)|IV]]\n| next_year  = 2011\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = III\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Just a Shock\n | single1date = May 8, 2009\n | single2     = Step Up (I'm On It)\n | single2date = August 11, 2009\n | single3     = Listen Close\n | single3date = March 29, 2011\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{rating|4|5}} <ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1573201}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]''\n| rev2Score =  {{Rating|1.5|5}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://altpress.com/reviews/III.htm |title=Alternative Press &#124; Reviews |publisher=Altpress.com |date= |accessdate=2012-02-24}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''III''''' is the third studio album by [[Maylene and the Sons of Disaster]]. It was released June 23, 2009, and all pre-orders shipped on June 18, 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view&friendId=5302690&blogId=492915797 |title=Pre Order the New Album Here. **OUT JUNE 23rd!** van Maylene and the Sons of Disaster op Myspace |publisher=Blogs.myspace.com |date=2009-06-04 |accessdate=2012-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207065936/http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view |archive-date=2009-02-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The first single from the album is Just A Shock, which was uploaded to the band's MySpace as a promo for the album. About a week before the album's release another song was released to the public: Step Up (I'm On It). On June 19 the album was leaked in its entirety onto the internet. The song \"Harvest Moon Hanging\" is a reference to the Harvest Moon from the ''[[Bone (comics)|Bone]]'' series (most notably collection six, ''[[Old Man's Cave]]''). The album debuted at number 71 on the Billboard 200 in its first week of release. It was announced that their song \"Step Up (I'm on It)\" was used as the official theme for the inaugural [[Bragging Rights (2009)|WWE Bragging Rights]] Pay-Per-View. In 2010, was released a Deluxe Edition of the album in iTunes, containing two new songs and the music video for \"Step Up (I'm on It)\". \"Step Up (I'm on It)\" also was on Season Two: Episode One of the critically acclaimed series \"[[Sons Of Anarchy]]\", when Bobby came back to the clubhouse after his jail time. \"Step Up (I'm on It) is also in the video game ''[[EA Sports MMA]]''.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{track listing\n| all_lyrics   = [[Dallas Taylor (vocalist)|Dallas Taylor]]\n| all_music    = [[Maylene and the Sons of Disaster]]\n| title1       = Waiting on My Deathbed\n| length1      = 4:03\n| title2       = Settling Scores by Burning Bridges\n| length2      = 3:52\n| title3       = Just a Shock\n| length3      = 3:13\n| title4       = Last Train Coming\n| length4      = 2:31\n| title5       = Step Up (I'm on It)\n| length5      = 3:28\n| title6       = Listen Close\n| length6      = 3:40\n| title7       = The Old Iron Hills\n| length7      = 2:33\n| title8       = No Good Son\n| length8      = 2:49\n| title9       = Harvest Moon Hanging\n| length9      = 3:24\n| title10      = Oh Lonely Grave\n| length10     = 3:24\n| title11      = The End is Here... The End Is Beautiful\n| length11     = 5:11\n| total_length = 38:56\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline  = Deluxe edition bonus tracks\n| collapsed = yes\n| title12   = Where the Saints Roam\n| length12  = 3:42\n| title13   = Cheap Thrills Cost the Most\n| length13  = 3:20\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n;Maylene and the Sons of Disaster\n* [[Dallas Taylor (vocalist)|Dallas Taylor]] \u2013 lead vocals, banjo, acoustic guitar on \"Where the Saints Roam\"\n* Chad Huff \u2013 lead guitar\n* Jake Duncan \u2013 rhythm guitar, vocals\n* Kelly Scott Nunn \u2013 rhythm guitar\n* Roman Haviland \u2013 bass\n* Matt Clark \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n;Additional personnel\n* Bethany Borg \u2013 violin\n* Jacob Bunton \u2013 banjo, mandolin, violin, additional vocals\n* Tim Carroll \u2013 bowed bass\n* Billy Grant \u2013 harmonica, additional vocals\n* Chris Griffin \u2013 dobro, lap steel guitar\n* Keith Harrison \u2013 additional vocals\n* Michael Swann \u2013 slide guitar\n* Barry Waldrep \u2013 banjo, lap steel guitar, dobro\n* Adam Wright \u2013 piano, string arrangements\n* Jason Elgin \u2013 engineer, production, mixing, percussion, additional vocals\n* Roger Lian \u2013 mastering\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Maylene and the Sons of Disaster}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Iii}}\n[[Category:2009 albums]]\n[[Category:Maylene and the Sons of Disaster albums|03]]\n", "name_user": "2601:8c3:8080:9c53:4063:8c05:694a:bafd", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/III_(Maylene_and_the_Sons_of_Disaster_album)"}
